# GPU Rig Monitoring Agent — Windows

Config file for the Windows agent. Place this file in the same directory as `run.py`.

## Fields

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `rig_uuid` | yes | Set to `"auto"` to generate a permanent UUID on first run. |
| `api_key` | yes | API key created from the monitoring dashboard. |
| `server_endpoint` | yes | The monitoring server URL, e.g. `https://monitor.example.com` (no trailing slash). |
| `expected_gpu_count` | no | `0` = auto-detect. Set to your actual GPU count to flag mismatches. |
| `collection_timeout_s` | no | Hard timeout in seconds (default: 45). |
| `retry_attempts` | no | Retries on transient failures (default: 3). |
| `debug_mode` | no | `true` = verbose logging + no gzip (default: `false`). |
